body:
When I build with `-MAKEFLAGS VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS=0` make flag, the Verilator build will fail with the following error message.
```
make: execvp: /bin/sh: Argument list too long
make: *** [/usr/local/share/verilator/include/verilated.mk:209: Vdbg_tpl_pkg__ALL.cpp] Error 127
make: *** Waiting for unfinished jobs....
make: Leaving directory '/workspace/uvm_debug/tpl_bug/obj_dir'
%Error: make -C obj_dir -f Vdbg_tpl_pkg.mk -j 16 VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS=0 exited with 2
%Error: Command Failed ulimit -s unlimited 2>/dev/null; exec /usr/local/share/verilator/bin/verilator_bin -j 16 --binary -top dbg_tpl_pkg -MAKEFLAGS VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS=0 tpl.sv
```

- Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

```systemverilog
//tpl.sv
package dbg_tpl_pkg;
    class tpl_object#(type T=int, string NAME = "");
        T t;
        function new(string name = NAME);
            this.t = $urandom_range(0, 100);
        endfunction

    endclass

// from 0 to 399
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_0") tpl_object_0;
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_1") tpl_object_1;
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_2") tpl_object_2;
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_3") tpl_object_3;
...
...
...
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_398") tpl_object_398;
typedef tpl_object#(int, "tpl_object_399") tpl_object_399;


endpackage
```

- What command line do we use to run your example?

```bash
verilator -j $(nproc) --binary -top dbg_tpl_pkg -MAKEFLAGS VM_PARALLEL_BUILDS=0 tpl.sv
```

- What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

Verilator 5.026 2024-06-15 rev v5.026

- What OS and distribution are you using?

Ubuntu 20.04.6 LTS
